]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The design follows the ISO 23247 reference architecture, mapping each Software Component (SW) to a Functional Entity (FE) and deploying each FE as an individual ROS2 package containing ROS2 nodes. The system is partitioned into three entities: the User Entity hosting the User Interface FE (split into 3D visualization and control panel), the Digital Twin Entity handling data management and control mechanisms, and the Physical Twin Entity encapsulating device communication, data preprocessing, actuation, and automotive functionality such as point‑cloud clustering and tracking. Resource management is handled through ROS2 middleware, which facilitates communication across distributed nodes, while a central entity aggregates data transformation and high‑level control, thereby coordinating the distributed twins."
]

