    base:desc "The Digital Twin Service is built on a hybrid network architecture. Software components within the same physical host communicate via ROS 2 over an internal bus, while inter‑entity communication (between the vehicle and the virtual twin) takes place over a Wi-Fi network using UDP. The system must honour a maximum network latency of 100 ms, as specified by Requirement R7. Bandwidth and reliability requirements beyond this latency constraint are not explicitly quantified. No explicit encryption or authentication protocols are specified for the network traffic in the provided documents."
