instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system aligns with the ISO 23247 – Digital twin framework for manufacturing. The reference architecture (Part 2 of the standard) specifies an entity‑based architecture comprising: Observable Manufacturing Element (OME), Data Collection and Device Control Entity, Digital Twin Entity, and User Entity, each composed of Functional Entities (FEs). The architecture supports digital representation of physical manufacturing elements (Part 3) and information exchange procedures (Part 4). Compliance is demonstrated by referencing the standard parts and by implementing data collection and control via OPC Unified Architecture, an interoperability protocol adopted by the standard."
